<div id="review_10545011" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/10545011" />
    <a title="Gemma Williams" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/633822-gemma-williams"><img alt="Gemma Williams" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1576865060p2/633822.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/10545011?book_show_action=true">Dec 17, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Gemma Williams" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Gemma Williams" href="/user/show/633822-gemma-williams">Gemma Williams</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140181524" href="/book/show/2302250.The_Knot_of_Vipers">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer10545011" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15307635944839708130">A brilliant and beautifully written study of greed, hypocrisy, jealousy and hatred, it conveys the corrosive effect of avarice through the story of an elderly man eaten up by hatred for the family who are all longing to get their hands on his money, and how he schemes to disinherit them. I especially like the contrast between the pious cliches of the family whose professed faith never makes the slightest difference to the way they live their lives, and the anti-religious miser who actually seems</span>
  <span id="freeText15307635944839708130" style="display:none">A brilliant and beautifully written study of greed, hypocrisy, jealousy and hatred, it conveys the corrosive effect of avarice through the story of an elderly man eaten up by hatred for the family who are all longing to get their hands on his money, and how he schemes to disinherit them. I especially like the contrast between the pious cliches of the family whose professed faith never makes the slightest difference to the way they live their lives, and the anti-religious miser who actually seems to have some kind of real spiritual awareness interwoven with his malice and stinginess. Fascinating and dark, and full of meaning and intelligence.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15307635944839708130" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


