<div id="review_38013994" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/38013994" />
    <a title="Hanne" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1507830-hanne"><img alt="Hanne" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1220991671p2/1507830.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/38013994?book_show_action=true">Nov 17, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hanne" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hanne" href="/user/show/1507830-hanne">Hanne</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9782253002871" href="/book/show/1547641.Le_N_ud_de_vip_res">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer38013994" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7910934608127216824">This is an intense drame of the life of a bourgoise family of Bordeaux in the beginning of the 20th century. More particularly, it is a letter written by an old man filled with hate of his family, his wife and their children. As a young he lost his hope of life and love as he learned that the wife married him to avoid a life as a celibataire and because of his money (she came from an old noble family which now didn&apos;t have anymore money, his family had money, but was not &quot;old&quot;). He thinks that hi</span>
  <span id="freeText7910934608127216824" style="display:none">This is an intense drame of the life of a bourgoise family of Bordeaux in the beginning of the 20th century. More particularly, it is a letter written by an old man filled with hate of his family, his wife and their children. As a young he lost his hope of life and love as he learned that the wife married him to avoid a life as a celibataire and because of his money (she came from an old noble family which now didn't have anymore money, his family had money, but was not "old"). He thinks that his family is waiting for his death, in fact, waiting for touching the heritage. And filled with vengeance, he writes this letter to them (which is the entire book), telling that there is no money for them and why it isn't. But since his wife dies before him, he loose this possibility of revenge. He refers to his own heart when he speaks about "le noued de vipère" or the nest of vipers. But indirectly, it is clear that also the family is also such a reference. Going through the book, the person also under the surface of the hate is shown, displaying a shy person with lack of self-confidence who has never been able to show love to others, and who has not been a person people want to give their love to either. Despite the main personnage's horrible behavior towards his family, the reader may get (more and more) pity with him. The other personnages have only secondary roles, and the descriptions of them are less profound. Nevertheless, the portrayals of human relationships are full of sensitivity and are touching. Also, the outer frame, with descriptions of this society, are highly approuved. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7910934608127216824" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


