<div id="review_1371842865" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1371842865" />
    <a title="John" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3131331-john"><img alt="John" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1547868152p2/3131331.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1371842865?book_show_action=true">Aug 23, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="John" class="user" itemprop="url" name="John" href="/user/show/3131331-john">John</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3131331-john?shelf=catholic">catholic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3131331-john?shelf=deep-thinking">deep-thinking</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/3131331-john?shelf=great-stuff">great-stuff</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1371842865" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8497367559791270291">HIGHLY RECOMMENDED. A selfish man, Louis, consumed by greed, by resentment, by desire for revenge. He loathes his wife, children and grandchildren. His heart is a tangle of vipers. His family waits for him to die and they are consumed by lust to inherit.They too are a tangle of vipers. He considers leaving them with nothing. This is a journal he writes near the end of his life. He explains his cold loveless life. As he nears death, he begins to see a distant light. It reminds me of <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/448899.The_Hound_of_Heaven' title='The Hound of Heaven by Francis Thompson' rel='nofollow noopener'>The Hound of </a></span>
  <span id="freeText8497367559791270291" style="display:none">HIGHLY RECOMMENDED. A selfish man, Louis, consumed by greed, by resentment, by desire for revenge. He loathes his wife, children and grandchildren. His heart is a tangle of vipers. His family waits for him to die and they are consumed by lust to inherit.They too are a tangle of vipers. He considers leaving them with nothing. This is a journal he writes near the end of his life. He explains his cold loveless life. As he nears death, he begins to see a distant light. It reminds me of <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/448899.The_Hound_of_Heaven" title="The Hound of Heaven by Francis Thompson" rel="nofollow noopener">The Hound of Heaven</a>. He was always pursued by someone, regardless of his worship of money and petty revenge. <br />Mauriac inspired Flannery O'Connor<a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/284996.The_Complete_Stories" title="The Complete Stories by Flannery O'Connor" rel="nofollow noopener">The Complete Stories</a>. This novel, like Flannery's stories, shows people at their worst. And sometimes it is at our worst when grace finally reaches us in our innermost being. Unlike <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/5326.A_Christmas_Carol" title="A Christmas Carol by Charles Dickens" rel="nofollow noopener">A Christmas Carol</a>, this is no feel good story. We are left to ponder whether Louis, after a lifetime of greed and bitterness, was redeemed. And Louis forces to me to look at my own life and ask whether I allow grace to work.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="8497367559791270291" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


