<div id="review_2469171715" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2469171715" />
    <a title="Jeff Lacy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4833799-jeff-lacy"><img alt="Jeff Lacy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442632305p2/4833799.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2469171715?book_show_action=true">Jul 25, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jeff Lacy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jeff Lacy" href="/user/show/4833799-jeff-lacy">Jeff Lacy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781944418267" href="/book/show/34082996-vipers-tangle">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2469171715" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8045911893981971824">Distilling the principles of Aristotelian Ethics, this novel evolves from a letter from a bitter old man to his wife and children and grandchildren, and his grievances against them for with-holding his fortune when he dies. This is a protagonist one may dislike or lack empathy. His justifications for him will be rational, to others irrational. One need to forebear judgement. No one is as bad as painted initially. That is one of the strengths of Mariac’s craft. He withholds motives or agendas or </span>
  <span id="freeText8045911893981971824" style="display:none">Distilling the principles of Aristotelian Ethics, this novel evolves from a letter from a bitter old man to his wife and children and grandchildren, and his grievances against them for with-holding his fortune when he dies. This is a protagonist one may dislike or lack empathy. His justifications for him will be rational, to others irrational. One need to forebear judgement. No one is as bad as painted initially. That is one of the strengths of Mariac’s craft. He withholds motives or agendas or the lack of agendas. Characters also evolve throughout the story. Hence, he moves the story forward with a well crafted plot and puts the characters in it and watches what happens. Economically written, austere, but robust thematically. It emits a strong narrow beam of light in the darkness. Mariac thus makes it easy to follow the path.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8045911893981971824" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


